INSERT INTO `grammar` VALUES (1,'2025-05-17 09:36:42.256595',_binary '','2025-06-03 17:47:53.319404','This lesson introduces the Simple Present Tense, one of the most basic and commonly used tenses in English. You will learn how to form it, when to use it, and how to apply it correctly in both affirmative and negative forms.','http://138.2.91.94:9000/h2t-english/grammar/1-0d2af5f1-d58e-40c6-848d-44e806c3dbf2','Simple Present Tense',2,'The Simple Present Tense is used to describe: Habits and routines, General truths and facts, Scheduled events (especially timetables), Feelings, thoughts, and states','I go to school every day.','http://138.2.91.94:9000/h2t-english/grammar/1-7eb847da-1d9b-400b-92da-de4072e975c2','7,8,9,10,11',NULL),(2,'2025-06-01 18:29:50.606433',_binary '','2025-06-04 09:33:19.869782','Learn how to use the Present Simple tense to talk about habits, general truths, and repeated actions.','http://138.2.91.94:9000/h2t-english/grammar/2-86154543-e90f-4bc6-8aa5-8b990e98777d','Present Simple Tense',2,'The Present Simple tense is used to describe habitual actions, general facts, and permanent situations.','She drinks coffee every morning.','http://138.2.91.94:9000/h2t-english/grammar/2-9f7b6ded-bdfb-4f75-ac0e-26ffae791ccb','30,31,32,33,34',NULL),(3,'2025-06-01 18:38:38.122511',_binary '','2025-06-03 15:29:51.987140','Learn how to use the Present Continuous Tense to talk about actions happening now or around the current time.','http://138.2.91.94:9000/h2t-english/grammar/3-d33c6a3e-0c77-4dc5-8e28-64fa4c80e6f0','Present Continuous Tense',0,'The Present Continuous Tense is used to describe actions that are happening right now or around the current time (but not necessarily at the exact moment of speaking).','She is reading a book right now.','http://138.2.91.94:9000/h2t-english/grammar/3-974fe689-fa0e-4ec3-bf6d-eec980d66b87','35,36,37,38,39',NULL),(4,'2025-06-01 18:47:24.397247',_binary '','2025-06-03 15:59:13.476128','Learn how to use the Simple Future Tense to talk about actions that will happen later.','http://138.2.91.94:9000/h2t-english/grammar/4-fc9cadd7-03e3-410e-9185-ff3c99eca7f4','Simple Future Tense',0,'The Simple Future Tense is used to describe actions that will happen later, often for predictions, promises, or spontaneous decisions. It is formed with \"will + base verb\" or \"be going to + base verb.\"','She will travel to Paris next month.','http://138.2.91.94:9000/h2t-english/grammar/4-f64a47b8-9223-444f-a76a-1747e59ee033','40,41,42,43,44',NULL),(5,'2025-06-01 18:53:55.458931',_binary '','2025-06-03 16:56:48.554138','Learn how to use the Simple Past Tense to talk about completed actions in the past.','http://138.2.91.94:9000/h2t-english/grammar/5-2ca5f6c0-02de-456e-a487-5a139c6453f2','Simple Past Tense',0,'The Simple Past Tense is used to describe actions that started and finished at a specific time in the past. Regular verbs form the past tense by adding \"-ed\", while irregular verbs have unique past forms.','She visited her grandparents last weekend.','http://138.2.91.94:9000/h2t-english/grammar/5-ca859fe7-4113-46ad-bdf2-9cf4a954026e','45,46,47,48,49',NULL),(6,'2025-06-01 19:23:55.810353',_binary '','2025-06-03 17:04:04.451561','Learn how to use the Present Perfect Tense to talk about past actions connected to the present.','http://138.2.91.94:9000/h2t-english/grammar/-1-7fd7d5e5-f282-44a8-9e67-caeba7e0ea14','Present Perfect Tense',0,'The Present Perfect Tense connects past actions to the present moment. It describes:Experiences in one\'s life, recently completed actions, actions that began in the past and continue now','I have visited Paris three times.','http://138.2.91.94:9000/h2t-english/grammar/6-b814bec3-4f13-48b6-9491-855bc97edf90','50,51,52,53,54',NULL);
