INSERT INTO `lesson_question` VALUES (1,'2025-05-17 09:26:42.131676',_binary '','2025-05-17 09:26:42.131690','What does the word \"pollution\" mean?','Pollution refers to the introduction of harmful materials into the environment, such as smoke, chemicals, or plastic, that cause damage to air, water, or land.'),(2,'2025-05-17 09:27:12.454890',_binary '','2025-05-17 09:27:12.454899','What is \"deforestation\"?','Deforestation means removing trees from forests on a large scale, often for farming or construction, which negatively impacts the environment and wildlife.'),(3,'2025-05-17 09:27:40.947095',_binary '','2025-05-17 09:27:40.947104','Which of the following is an example of recycling?','Recycling involves processing used materials (like bottles or cans) so they can be used again, reducing waste and saving resources.'),(4,'2025-05-17 09:28:09.856554',_binary '','2025-05-17 09:28:09.856566','What does the word \"sustainable\" refer to?','Sustainable practices are those that meet current needs without harming future generations or the planet, such as using renewable energy or reducing waste.'),(5,'2025-05-17 09:28:36.708584',_binary '','2025-05-17 09:28:36.708592','What is a greenhouse effect?','The greenhouse effect happens when gases like CO₂ trap heat in the Earth\'s atmosphere, leading to an increase in global temperatures.'),(6,'2025-05-17 09:29:05.075906',_binary '','2025-05-17 09:29:05.075915','What is climate change mostly caused by?','Climate change is largely caused by human actions such as burning coal, oil, and gas, which release greenhouse gases and affect global climate patterns.'),(7,'2025-05-17 09:38:09.865470',_binary '','2025-05-17 09:38:09.865489','Which sentence is in the correct simple present form?','In the simple present tense, we add -es to the verb when the subject is he/she/it. → \"goes\"'),(8,'2025-05-17 09:38:35.903816',_binary '','2025-05-17 09:38:35.903825','What is the negative form of: “He eats vegetables”?','In the negative form, use “doesn’t + base verb”. No -s after the verb.'),(9,'2025-05-17 09:39:04.494281',_binary '','2025-05-17 09:39:04.494291','Which question is correct in the simple present tense?','Use “Does + subject + base verb” for yes/no questions. Never add -s to the main verb in a question.'),(10,'2025-05-17 09:39:31.457638',_binary '','2025-05-17 09:39:31.457648','What time expression is commonly used with the simple present tense?','\"Every morning\" refers to a regular action, which is typical for the simple present.'),(11,'2025-05-17 09:39:58.224039',_binary '','2025-05-17 09:39:58.224056','Which of the following shows a habit?','Habits are described using the simple present with time expressions like \"every morning\".'),(12,'2025-05-17 09:48:24.305560',_binary '','2025-05-17 09:48:24.305587','Where does Anna go on Sunday?','The passage states that Anna goes to the park on Sunday.'),(13,'2025-05-17 09:49:04.636402',_binary '','2025-05-17 09:49:04.636412','What does Anna bring to the park?','Anna brings a book and a sandwich to the park, as mentioned in the passage.'),(14,'2025-05-17 10:18:36.828268',_binary '','2025-05-17 10:18:36.828290','What does Emma want to cook with the vegetables she is buying?',' In the conversation, Emma asks the vendor \"And what would you recommend for a stir-fry?\" '),(15,'2025-06-01 16:27:02.385928',_binary '','2025-06-01 16:27:02.385939','What do you call a piece of furniture used for sitting?','This question asks for the name of a common household item where people sit.'),(16,'2025-06-01 16:27:27.719711',_binary '','2025-06-01 16:27:27.719722','Which item is used to store food at a low temperature?','The correct answer is the appliance that keeps food cold.'),(17,'2025-06-01 16:27:54.952670',_binary '','2025-06-01 16:27:54.952678','Where would you look to see your reflection?','This item shows your image when you look at it.'),(18,'2025-06-01 16:28:20.527876',_binary '','2025-06-01 16:28:20.527885','What is a long, comfortable seat for multiple people called?','This piece of furniture is usually found in living rooms.'),(19,'2025-06-01 16:28:53.162080',_binary '','2025-06-01 16:28:53.162106','Which item provides light in a dark room?','The correct answer is an object that produces light.'),(20,'2025-06-01 16:54:42.789686',_binary '','2025-06-01 16:54:42.789696','Which verb means \"to share information or ideas with others\"?','This action involves exchanging messages.'),(21,'2025-06-01 16:55:08.702328',_binary '','2025-06-01 16:55:08.702337','What is the opposite of speaking loudly?','This verb describes speaking very softly.'),(22,'2025-06-01 16:55:36.790050',_binary '','2025-06-01 16:55:36.790059','Which adjective describes someone who is respectful and considerate?','This word describes good manners.'),(23,'2025-06-01 16:56:07.116443',_binary '','2025-06-01 16:56:07.116452','What adverb means \"in a way that is easy to understand\"?','This describes speaking without confusion.'),(24,'2025-06-01 16:56:32.720768',_binary '','2025-06-01 16:56:32.720778','Which word means \"to convince someone to do something\"?',' This verb involves changing someone’s opinion.'),(25,'2025-06-01 18:10:43.740053',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:10:43.740066','What is the purpose of a salutation in a letter?','It introduces the recipient at the beginning.'),(26,'2025-06-01 18:11:06.577852',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:11:06.577862','Which word means \"to add a file to an email\"?','This action includes supplementary documents.'),(27,'2025-06-01 18:11:31.251597',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:11:31.251608','How should a job application email be written?','It requires professional language.'),(28,'2025-06-01 18:11:59.730796',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:11:59.730807','Which adverb is commonly used in letter closings?','It expresses genuine feelings.'),(29,'2025-06-01 18:12:26.209779',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:12:26.209792','What should you include to identify the email\'s content quickly?','It summarizes the email’s purpose.'),(30,'2025-06-01 18:32:28.728160',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:32:28.728172','Which sentence is correct?','The correct answer is B because, in the Present Simple tense, for he/she/it, we add -s/-es to the verb. \"Go\" becomes \"goes\" for the third-person singular.'),(31,'2025-06-01 18:33:01.206210',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:33:01.206219','What is the negative form of \"They play football\"?','The correct answer is C because, in negative Present Simple sentences, we use \"do not\" (don’t) or \"does not\" (doesn’t) before the base verb. Since \"they\" is plural, we use \"don’t.\"'),(32,'2025-06-01 18:33:33.303139',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:33:33.303150','Which sentence describes a general truth?','The correct answer is B because general truths (facts that are always true) use the Present Simple tense. \"Cats drink milk\" is a general fact, while the other options describe temporary actions or past events.'),(33,'2025-06-01 18:34:07.094227',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:34:07.094240','Choose the correct question form:','The correct answer is B because, in Present Simple questions with he/she/it, we use \"Does\" + base verb (like). \"Do he likes\" is incorrect because \"does\" already indicates the third person, so the verb should remain in its base form.'),(34,'2025-06-01 18:34:44.239510',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:34:44.239520','Which sentence is incorrect?','The correct answer is B because \"studies\" is incorrect for the subject \"we.\" The correct form should be \"study\" since plural subjects (we/you/they) do not take -s/-es in the Present Simple.'),(35,'2025-06-01 18:39:18.010467',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:39:18.010479','Which sentence is correct in the Present Continuous Tense?','The Present Continuous requires \"am/is/are + verb-ing.\" Only option B follows this rule.'),(36,'2025-06-01 18:39:51.908162',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:39:51.908183','What is the correct form of the verb in this sentence?\n\n\"They ___________ football in the park.\"','The subject \"They\" requires \"are + verb-ing.\"'),(37,'2025-06-01 18:40:28.523697',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:40:28.523717','Which time expression is NOT commonly used with Present Continuous?','\"Yesterday\" refers to the past, while Present Continuous describes current actions.'),(38,'2025-06-01 18:40:59.813586',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:40:59.813596','Choose the sentence that describes a future plan.','Present Continuous can describe future plans when a time reference (e.g., \"tonight\") is given.'),(39,'2025-06-01 18:41:32.475494',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:41:32.475503','Which sentence is INCORRECT in Present Continuous?','Verbs like \"like,\" \"love,\" \"know,\" and \"believe\" are stative and rarely used in continuous forms.'),(40,'2025-06-01 18:48:00.018857',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:48:00.018880','Which sentence is correct in the Simple Future Tense?','The Simple Future requires \"will + base verb\" or \"be going to + base verb.\"'),(41,'2025-06-01 18:48:47.662464',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:48:47.662474','What is the correct form of the verb in this sentence?\nWe ___________ a movie tonight.','The Simple Future uses \"will\" or \"be going to\" before the base verb.'),(42,'2025-06-01 18:49:07.275377',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:49:07.275394','Which time expression is NOT commonly used with Simple Future?','Simple Future refers to later events, not past or habitual actions.'),(43,'2025-06-01 18:49:36.597085',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:49:36.597097','Choose the sentence that describes a spontaneous decision.','\"Will\" is often used for quick decisions made at the moment.'),(44,'2025-06-01 18:50:00.527821',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:50:00.527826','Which sentence is INCORRECT in Simple Future?','\"Will\" should be followed by a base verb, not past tense.'),(45,'2025-06-01 18:54:52.052280',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:54:52.052300','Which sentence is correct in the Simple Past Tense?','The Simple Past describes completed actions, often with past time expressions.'),(46,'2025-06-01 18:55:16.856941',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:55:16.856952','What is the correct past form of the verb in this sentence? She ___________ her homework before dinner.','Regular verbs add \"-ed\"; irregular verbs have unique past forms.'),(47,'2025-06-01 18:55:39.158467',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:55:39.158472','Which time expression is NOT used with the Simple Past?','Simple Past refers to finished actions, not present or future times.'),(48,'2025-06-01 18:56:00.504870',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:56:00.504875','Choose the sentence that uses an irregular past tense verb correctly.','Irregular verbs (e.g., \"write → wrote\") don’t follow the \"-ed\" rule.'),(49,'2025-06-01 18:56:24.609765',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:56:24.609771','Which sentence is INCORRECT in the Simple Past?','The past form must match the verb type (regular/irregular).'),(50,'2025-06-01 19:24:21.966915',_binary '','2025-06-01 19:24:21.966924','Which sentence correctly uses Present Perfect?','This tense connects past actions to the present moment.'),(51,'2025-06-01 19:24:45.812917',_binary '','2025-06-01 19:24:45.812923','What is the correct form of the verb? He ___________ that book three times.','Present Perfect uses \"have/has\" + past participle.'),(52,'2025-06-01 19:25:09.509097',_binary '','2025-06-01 19:25:09.509105','Which time expression is NOT used with Present Perfect?','Present Perfect doesn\'t use specific past time references.'),(53,'2025-06-01 19:25:38.857171',_binary '','2025-06-01 19:25:38.857185','Choose the sentence showing a continuing action from past to present.','\"Since\" indicates an action that started in the past and continues.'),(54,'2025-06-01 19:31:45.181894',_binary '','2025-06-01 19:31:45.181912','Which sentence is INCORRECT in Present Perfect?','The past participle form must be used correctly.'),(55,'2025-06-01 21:44:18.677938',_binary '','2025-06-01 21:44:18.677980','Why does Emma ask Jack to put his bottle in the recycling bin?','Emma mentions that littering harms animals, emphasizing environmental responsibility.'),(56,'2025-06-01 21:44:46.218511',_binary '','2025-06-01 21:44:46.218534','What does Lisa think about Emma’s volunteer work?','Lisa says, \"More people should do this!\" showing support.'),(57,'2025-06-01 21:45:14.826276',_binary '','2025-06-01 21:45:14.826296','How often does Emma’s group organize clean-up events?','Emma states, \"We organize clean-up events every month.\"'),(58,'2025-06-01 21:45:45.021201',_binary '','2025-06-01 21:45:45.021232','What is one problem caused by plastic waste in the park?','Emma explains that plastic waste \"can hurt wildlife.\"'),(59,'2025-06-01 21:46:17.141699',_binary '','2025-06-01 21:46:17.141716','What does Lisa say she might do in the future?','Lisa says, \"Maybe I’ll join next time!\" showing interest in volunteering.'),(60,'2025-06-01 22:24:22.900356',_binary '','2025-06-01 22:24:22.900368','What is Jake’s main concern about the exam?','Jake mentions that he still needs to review the formulas, indicating he doesn’t feel fully prepared.'),(61,'2025-06-01 22:24:48.469253',_binary '','2025-06-01 22:24:48.469261','How does Emma feel about the exam?','Emma says she’s been practicing but is still nervous.'),(62,'2025-06-01 22:25:17.792335',_binary '','2025-06-01 22:25:17.792348','What do they decide to do before the exam?','They agree to meet early to review one more time.'),(63,'2025-06-01 22:25:44.419761',_binary '','2025-06-01 22:25:44.419770','What tool does Jake mention using during the exam?','Jake talks about using a calculator for complex calculations.'),(64,'2025-06-01 22:26:11.247708',_binary '','2025-06-01 22:26:11.247716','What emotion do both students share?','Both admit feeling nervous or anxious about the exam.'),(65,'2025-06-02 13:51:47.652342',_binary '','2025-06-02 13:51:47.652369','What is the maximum resolution supported by the new console?','The presenter specifically mentions \"true 8K resolution\" as a feature.'),(66,'2025-06-0