aveled to more than thirty countries,\" using present perfect tense to describe her experiences up to the present moment.'),(261,'2025-06-03 22:34:50.996961',_binary '','2025-06-03 22:34:50.996976','What has forced families in Bangladesh to abandon their homes?','The speaker explains \"Rising sea levels have forced entire families to abandon their ancestral homes,\" using present perfect tense to describe the ongoing impact of climate change.'),(262,'2025-06-03 22:35:20.817039',_binary '','2025-06-03 22:35:20.817058','What did Maria witness in Norway?','Maria mentions \"In Norway, I witnessed cities that run entirely on renewable energy,\" using simple present tense to describe the current state of these cities.'),(263,'2025-06-03 22:35:52.677963',_binary '','2025-06-03 22:35:52.677972','According to Maria, what do we need to implement solutions on a larger scale?','She states \"we need political will, financial investment, and global cooperation to implement them on a larger scale,\" using simple present tense to express current necessity.'),(264,'2025-06-03 22:36:22.797287',_binary '','2025-06-03 22:36:22.797305','What does Maria say about the timing of action on climate change?','Maria emphasizes \"We must act with the knowledge we have right now,\" using modal verb \"must\" to express urgent necessity in the present.'),(265,'2025-06-03 23:13:08.442554',_binary '','2025-06-03 23:13:08.442575','According to Dr. Chen, what has transformed faster than most experts predicted?','Dr. Chen states \"Artificial intelligence has transformed from science fiction into everyday reality faster than most experts predicted,\" using present perfect tense to describe the rapid development.'),(266,'2025-06-03 23:13:42.184601',_binary '','2025-06-03 23:13:42.184613','What does Dr. Chen believe about the next breakthrough in AI?','He states \"The next breakthrough will likely come from combining different types of artificial intelligence,\" using future tense with modal verb \"will\" to express prediction.'),(267,'2025-06-03 23:14:10.018985',_binary '','2025-06-03 23:14:10.018996','In which timeframe does Dr. Chen predict AI will revolutionize personalized medicine?','Dr. Chen specifically mentions \"In the next five years, I predict that AI will revolutionize personalized medicine,\" using simple future tense for prediction.'),(268,'2025-06-03 23:14:34.632494',_binary '','2025-06-03 23:14:34.632506','What do current AI systems lack according to the lecture?','He explains that current systems \"lack general intelligence\" and \"cannot transfer knowledge from one domain to another,\" using simple present tense to describe current limitations.'),(269,'2025-06-03 23:15:02.834816',_binary '','2025-06-03 23:15:02.834849','What does Dr. Chen say is key to successful AI development?','He concludes \"The key to successful AI development lies in interdisciplinary collaboration,\" using simple present tense to state his opinion.'),(270,'2025-06-03 23:19:56.645430',_binary '','2025-06-03 23:19:56.645464','How long ago did Rebecca Martinez start her career?','She mentions \"When I started my career twenty-five years ago,\" using simple past tense to reference a specific time in the past.'),(271,'2025-06-03 23:20:25.674689',_binary '','2025-06-03 23:20:25.674702','By what average percentage have companies with strong ESG practices outperformed competitors?','Martinez states \"Companies with strong environmental, social, and governance practices have outperformed their competitors by an average of 15%,\" using present perfect tense to describe performance over time.'),(272,'2025-06-03 23:20:49.796967',_binary '','2025-06-03 23:20:49.796978','When did her company implement their sustainability program?','She clearly states \"Five years ago, we implemented a comprehensive sustainability program,\" using simple past tense with a specific time reference.'),(273,'2025-06-03 23:21:16.683927',_binary '','2025-06-03 23:21:16.683937','What does Martinez call the leadership approach where companies leave the world better than they found it?','She introduces the concept saying \"I believe businesses must embrace what I call \'regenerative leadership,\'\" using present tense to define her term.'),(274,'2025-06-03 23:21:39.751892',_binary '','2025-06-03 23:21:39.751901','What has her company\'s sustainability program achieved according to the speech?','She explains the program \"has saved us millions of dollars in operational costs while improving our brand reputation and employee satisfaction,\" using present perfect tense to describe cumulative results.'),(275,'2025-06-03 23:24:37.980979',_binary '','2025-06-03 23:24:37.981031','How long has Dr. Thompson been studying climate patterns and adaptation?','Dr. Thompson introduces herself saying \"I have been studying climate patterns and adaptation mechanisms for the past fifteen years,\" using present perfect continuous tense.'),(276,'2025-06-03 23:25:04.897476',_binary '','2025-06-03 23:25:04.897489','According to the economic analysis, how much money does every dollar spent on climate adaptation save?','She states \"Economic analyses show that every dollar spent on climate adaptation saves between four and seven dollars in future damage costs,\" using simple present tense for factual information.'),(277,'2025-06-03 23:25:32.356872',_binary '','2025-06-03 23:25:32.356883','By how much have precision farming techniques increased crop yields?','Dr. Thompson mentions \"These innovations have increased crop yields by up to 30%,\" using present perfect tense to describe achieved results.'),(278,'2025-06-03 23:25:56.047016',_binary '','2025-06-03 23:25:56.047030','What is the approximate cost of mangrove restoration per hectare in Vietnam?','She provides specific cost data: \"A mangrove restoration project in Vietnam costs approximately $1,000 per hectare,\" using simple present tense for current pricing.'),(279,'2025-06-03 23:26:22.395365',_binary '','2025-06-03 23:26:22.395377','According to Dr. Thompson, how much time do we have to implement large-scale adaptation measures?','She warns \"We have perhaps ten to fifteen years to implement large-scale adaptation measures,\" using simple present tense to express urgency about the timeline.');
